<bug>
	<id>45518</id>
	<title>FILESAVE: rectangle rounded corners not saved</title>
	<description>
		<paragraph id="1">
			<sentence id="1.1">Problem description: 
After creating a rectangle with rounded corners (e.g. select shape, right click -&gt; Position and size... -&gt; Slant &amp; Corner Radius -&gt; Radius = 1") and saving the presentation.</sentence>
			<sentence id="1.2">The corners are back to square after reopening the presentation.</sentence>
		</paragraph>
		<paragraph id="2">
			<sentence id="2.1">Steps to reproduce:</sentence>
			<sentence id="2.2">1 Add rounded-corner rectangle to some slide.</sentence>
			<sentence id="2.3">2 Save and close the presentation.</sentence>
			<sentence id="2.4">3 Reopen the presentation, observe the corners are now square.</sentence>
		</paragraph>
		<paragraph id="3">
			<sentence id="3.1">Current behavior:
Corners do not preserve rounded-ness.</sentence>
			<sentence id="3.2">Expected behavior:
I expect the shapes to be preserved over closing/opening of files.</sentence>
			<sentence id="3.3">Platform (if different from the browser): 
              
Browser: Mozilla/5.0 (Windows NT 5.1; rv:9.0.1) Gecko/20100101 Firefox/9.0.1</sentence>
		</paragraph>
	</description>
